into these shoes.

11
00:00:33,133 --> 00:00:35,538
So Ralph got weird sneakers...
Who cares?

12
00:00:35,638 --> 00:00:37,809
Uh, no one...

13
00:00:37,876 --> 00:00:39,713
except everyone.

14
00:00:39,780 --> 00:00:41,617
Those aren't just sneakers.

15
00:00:41,684 --> 00:00:43,053
They're Slipremes.

16
00:00:43,186 --> 00:00:45,692
That's Orion Hughes'
skatewear company.

17
00:00:45,792 --> 00:00:48,263
He's huge on TikTok.

18
00:00:48,363 --> 00:00:50,467
Got to say, today was crazy.

19
00:00:50,568 --> 00:00:52,071
You all know my dad,

20
00:00:52,137 --> 00:00:54,342
international superstar
Darius Hughes.

21
00:00:54,375 --> 00:00:56,780
Well, I just laid down the hook
for his new movie,

22
00:00:56,847 --> 00:00:59,519
Duplicate Cop 2: Copy Cop.

23
00:01:08,236 --> 00:01:10,240
And my skatewear brand, Slipreme,

24
00:01:10,340 --> 00:01:12,177
is about to drop a new shoe,

25
00:01:12,244 --> 00:01:14,482
the sequel to the Caliphate One.

26
00:01:14,583 --> 00:01:16,152
The Caliphate Two.

27
00:01:16,219 --> 00:01:18,958
Limited release...
Available only this Friday.

28
00:01:19,025 --> 00:01:20,528
And Saturday,

29
00:01:20,595 --> 00:01:23,099
we explode the pop-up factory
that makes them.

30
00:01:23,199 --> 00:01:26,707
Go! Go! Go, Orion! Go! Go!

31
00:01:26,774 --> 00:01:28,443
Go! Go! Go, popcorn!

32
00:01:28,511 --> 00:01:30,848
Go! Go! Go, popcorn!

33
00:01:30,915 --> 00:01:32,986
No! No! No kernels!

34
00:01:33,119 --> 00:01:35,858
No! No! No kernels!

35
00:01:35,925 --> 00:01:37,361
Hey, that's my favorite show.

36
00:01:37,428 --> 00:01:39,465
You guys have to buy me
these sneakers.

37
00:01:39,533 --> 00:01:41,369
They're all anyone
cares about at school.

38
00:01:41,436 --> 00:01:43,173
And if I don't have them,
I'm nobody.

39
00:01:43,239 --> 00:01:45,444
Well, you're somebody
in this house.

40
00:01:45,511 --> 00:01:47,682
Come on, don't lie to the boy.

41
00:01:47,749 --> 00:01:49,485
I've never wanted
a piece of clothing before

42
00:01:49,586 --> 00:01:51,055
in my entire life.

43
00:01:51,122 --> 00:01:52,659
Dad, with this one act,

44
00:01:52,726 --> 00:01:55,898
you can erase ten years
of second-rate parenting.

45
00:01:55,965 --> 00:01:57,368
I'd think about that, Homie.

46
00:01:57,434 --> 00:01:59,005
It's a pretty good offer.

47
00:02:00,374 --> 00:02:03,380
You must really want those pants

48
00:02:03,514 --> 00:02:05,017
or videogame.

49
00:02:05,117 --> 00:02:08,289
Son, your father will deliver.

50
00:02:11,530 --> 00:02:14,068
Of course Orion Hughes'
new store would be

51
00:02:14,168 --> 00:02:16,907
in Springfield's
former packing peanuts district.

52
00:02:17,041 --> 00:02:18,978
This street is so cool.

53
00:02:19,045 --> 00:02:21,349
Art galleries,
beard-only barbershops,

54
00:02:21,416 --> 00:02:23,353
and a weird store
that only sells

55
00:02:23,420 --> 00:02:25,625
a single action figure.

56
00:02:25,692 --> 00:02:27,428
How do they survive?

57
00:02:30,835 --> 00:02:32,972
Oh, look at this line.

58
00:02:33,073 --> 00:02:34,843
Can't even see those guys.

59
00:02:34,943 --> 00:02:38,049
I'm gonna be stuck here all day
with the nose ring brigade.

60
00:02:38,116 --> 00:02:42,391
In that case, I'm gonna check
out this Hasidic surfwear shop.

61
00:02:43,561 --> 00:02:46,099
Okay, Homer, you can do this...
You waited in line overnight

62
00:02:46,199 --> 00:02:48,103
for Krusty's
new fried chicken sandwich.

63
00:02:48,203 --> 00:02:51,376
And it was the best decision
of your life.

64
00:02:51,476 --> 00:02:54,348
I will get Bart those shoes.

65
00:03:00,327 --> 00:03:02,966
Dad, you got 'em.

66
00:03:03,033 --> 00:03:05,337
I waited through rain,
through sun,

67
00:03:05,437 --> 00:03:07,341
through the death
of my phone battery

68
00:03:07,441 --> 00:03:09,980
from watching super-cuts
of boating accident videos,

69
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:13,521
all to see the joy on your face.

70
00:03:13,621 --> 00:03:16,860
I love you, Dad.
I finally love you.

71
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:18,229
And bought love

72
00:03:18,329 --> 00:03:21,269
is the best kind of love.

73
00:03:21,402 --> 00:03:22,739
- Wow!
- I'm so pumped!

74
00:03:22,839 --> 00:03:23,941
I'm also pumped!

75
00:03:24,041 --> 00:03:26,145
Here come the sneakers!

76
00:03:32,759 --> 00:03:35,965
Whoa, I got to see
those babies in action.

77
00:03:46,352 --> 00:03:48,256
These shoes are made from...

78
00:03:48,323 --> 00:03:52,164
- used Band-
- Aids and North Korean newspapers?

79
00:03:52,197 --> 00:03:54,034
My dad waited in line
all day for these shoes,

80
00:03:54,101 --> 00:03:55,337
and they're crap.

81
00:03:55,404 --> 00:03:58,276
I'm gonna go to that store
and get his money back.

82
